name: ethanol production from whey | protein feed, 100% crude | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/10797/documentation

The multioutput-process "whey, to fermentation" delivers the co-products Ethanol, 95% in H20, from whey",  "yeast paste from whey", and "portein concentrate rom whey". The allocation is based on economic criteria. The production of ethanol from whey is of no economical importance in the world.;[This dataset is meant to replace the following datasets:; - treatment of whey by fermentation, GLO, 2000 - 2004 (c9b1398f-a03d-41ed-8036-a2a92fc089e6)]



Fermentation of whey including materials, energy uses, infrastructure, and emissions.
category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/201:Manufacture of basic chemicals, fertilizers and nitrogen compounds, plastics/2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: The inventory is modelled with data from a plant in Ireland.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Production of ethanol from whey with the Carbery process.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Some data are derived from other or unknown plants or have been estimated. This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography CH. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
